This paper deals with the problem of detecting avian flight calls from bioacoustic sensor networks using machine learning techniques. The paper focuses on improving the generalizability of sound event detection models across heterogeneous acoustic environments. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing). Additionally, the paper uses several machine learning techniques, including convolutional neural networks (CNN), per-channel energy normalization (PCEN), and context-adaptive neural network (CA-NN) layer. Therefore, it is also likely to belong to cs.SI (Signal Processing), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.CV (Computer Vision).
